OL,6,FThe mother and her son eventually
OL,7,Freported Dawson to .
OL,9,FSheffield Crown Court heard how
OL,10,FDawson, 35, became involved with the
OL,11,Fpair after the woman - an alcoholic
OL,12,Fwith mental health issues - asked to
OL,13,Fborrow #5 for cider.
OL,15,FHer son would also use Dawson's
OL,16,Fillegal services.
OL,18,FSimon Mortimer, prosecuting, told the
OL,19,Fcourt he would hand over all his
OL,20,Fbenefits. Dawson would use his bank
OL,21,Fcard to get money.
