OL,6,FOn one occasion, in May 2022, the man
OL,7,Fdid not have enough funds to repay
OL,8,FDawson who then assaulted him,
OL,9,Ffracturing his jaw.
OL,11,FPart of the man's jaw "came away", Mr
OL,12,FMortimer said. He ended up "pulling it
OL,13,Fthrough his cheek."
OL,15,FSocial services then intervened and
OL,16,Frelocated the pair, but Dawson found
OL,17,Fthem after using violence to
OL,18,F"interrogate" the man. He then went to
OL,19,Ftheir new house and attacked them both.
