OL,6,FThe court heard following his arrest,
OL,7,Fa number of items were seized from
OL,8,FDawson's home, including his mobile
OL,9,Fphone.
OL,11,FHis and his wife's bank accounts
OL,12,Fshowed evidence of money lending.
OL,14,FThe court heard that there were at
OL,15,Fleast 88 different customers or people
OL,16,Fwho were being "terrorised" by Dawson.
OL,17,FRepayments came to a total of #52,000.
OL,19,FDawson was on licence for robbery at
OL,20,Fthe time. Mr Mortimer said he had
OL,21,Fprevious convictions for wounding.
